# User area: layout & list pages

## Page container padding (small screens)

- Main content wrapper on user pages must use **responsive padding** so small screens have less padding.
- Use: `p: { xs: 2, sm: 3 }` (not fixed `p: 3`).
- Applies to: any full-page Box with `bgcolor: bggrayColor`, `minHeight: "100vh"` (e.g. ContactSubmissionPage, DashboardView, ServicesPage, ClientsPage, FaqsPage, AdminsPage, CategoryPage, ProjectPages, TestimonialsPage, DashboardSkeleton).

## Contact submissions & similar list pages (search + filters + table)

### Filter row (search + date)

- **Same line on small screens:** Filter row must keep search input and date dropdown on one line. Use `flexWrap: "nowrap"`, search field `flex: { xs: "1 1 0", sm: "none" }` and `minWidth: 0`, date control `flexShrink: 0` and `minWidth: { xs: 120, sm: 160 }`. No separate "Date" label above the dropdown (no `InputLabel`; use `Select` with `displayEmpty` only).
- **Date filter logic:** "Today" = submissions from start of today to end of today (exclude future). "Last 7 days" / "Last 30 days" = from that many days ago up to now (exclude future). Use `todayStart`, `todayEnd` (23:59:59), and cap at `now` for 7/30.
- **Search:** Filter by fullName, email, phone, message, companyName, address (case-insensitive). Show "X result(s)" when search or date filter is active.

### Table on small screens

- Wrap table in a Box with `overflowX: "auto"` and `width: "100%"`. Table: `minWidth: 720` so it scrolls horizontally on narrow viewports.
- Header cells: use `whiteSpace: "nowrap"` and sensible `minWidth` (e.g. Name 120, Email 160, Phone 100, Message 140, Date 100) so "Message" and "Date" headings are always visible when scrolling.

## Styling

- Use project tokens: `bggrayColor`, `bordergrayColor`, `primaryColor`. Table pagination and buttons: same style as other user pages (border gray, purple hover).
